  "abstract": "Cracking clay soils (Vertisols and their intergrades) [Soil Survey Staff 2006] are\r\nimportant natural resources in a wide range of climatic zones, from humid tropical to\r\narid dry areas of the world [Ahmad 1996]. The natural vegetation of these areas is dry\r\ndeciduous forest. However, most of the soils are now under cultivation. Soils of these\r\nclimates have a significant role in the agricultural resource inventory of countries\r\nsuch as Australia, India, the Caribbean Islands,...............",
